'''Bradley Jean-Manuel Essolisam Addo Barcola''' ({{IPA|fr|bʁɑdlɛ bɑʁkɔlɑ}}; born 2 September 2002) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{French football updater|PSG}} club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]]. He is known for his speed and dribbling.

After coming up through [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]'s academy, Barcola began his professional career with his boyhood club, where he would play two seasons, the latter of which he broke out into the starting squad, leading the club in [[Assist (association football)|assists]]. In 2023, he signed for Paris Saint-Germain for a €45 million transfer fee, where he went on to win the [[UEFA Champions League]] as part of a continental treble in 2025.

Barcola played youth international football for France at [[France national under-21 football team|under-21]] and [[France Olympic football team|Olympic]] levels. He made his senior international debut in June 2024, and was a member of the France squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

==Early life==
Bradley Jean-Manuel Essolisam Addo Barcola<ref name="PSG Profile"/> was born on 2 September 2002 in [[Villeurbanne]], a commune in the Metropolis of Lyon,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur83812.html |title=Bradley Barcola |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=7 October 2023 |language=fr}}</ref> to a French mother and Togolese father.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|last=Hattabi|first=Dahbia|date=17 January 2020|title=Officiel : Bradley Barcola signe un contrat stagiaire à l'OL|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a4114822484274210995-officiel-bradley-barcola-signe-un-contrat-stagiaire-a-lol|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=Foot Mercato|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104215339/https://www.footmercato.net/a4114822484274210995-officiel-bradley-barcola-signe-un-contrat-stagiaire-a-lol |archive-date=4 November 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Hattabi|first=Dahbia|date=21 February 2020|title=Coupe Gambardella : ces cinq pépites qui font le bonheur de l'Olympique Lyonnais|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a6865778485539471419-coupe-gambardella-ces-cinq-pepites-qui-font-le-bonheur-de-lolympique-lyonnais|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=Foot Mercato|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104215339/https://www.footmercato.net/a6865778485539471419-coupe-gambardella-ces-cinq-pepites-qui-font-le-bonheur-de-lolympique-lyonnais |archive-date=4 November 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|date=13 September 2021|title=OL : premier contrat professionnel pour l'attaquant Bradley Barcola|url=https://www.leprogres.fr/sport/2021/09/13/ol-premier-contrat-professionnel-pour-l-attaquant-bradley-barcola|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=[[Le Progrès]]|language=FR-fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210914140319/https://www.leprogres.fr/sport/2021/09/13/ol-premier-contrat-professionnel-pour-l-attaquant-bradley-barcola |archive-date=14 September 2021 }}</ref> He started playing football in his home town, before joining [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] at the age of eight.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

==Club career==
===Lyon===
During the [[2020–21 Olympique Lyonnais season|2020–21 season]] Barcola started playing with the [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|Lyon reserve]] in [[Championnat National 2|National 2]] while also being a prolific goalscorer with the under-19 who played in the [[2020–21 UEFA Youth League|UEFA Youth League]],<ref name=":0" /> before signing a junior contract in January 2021.<ref name=":2" />

After being called up to the Lyon first team by [[Peter Bosz]] during the [[2021–22 Olympique Lyonnais season#Pre-season and friendlies|2021–22 pre-season]]—scoring his first goal against [[Football Bourg-en-Bresse Péronnas 01|Bourg-en-Bresse]]<ref>{{Cite web|date=12 July 2021|title=Après OL – Bourg : les jeunes dans tous les bons coups|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2021/07/12/apres-ol-bourg-les-jeunes-dans-tous-les-bons-coups|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=OL.fr|language=fr-FR|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210714092813/https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2021/07/12/apres-ol-bourg-les-jeunes-dans-tous-les-bons-coups |archive-date=14 July 2021 }}</ref>— Barcola signed his first professional contract in September 2021, tying him to the club until 2024.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|date=13 September 2021|title=Bradley Barcola signe son 1er contrat professionnel avec l'OL jusqu'en 2024|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2021/09/13/prolongation-barcola|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=OL.fr|language=fr-FR|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210917030216/https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2021/09/13/prolongation-barcola |archive-date=17 September 2021 }}</ref>

Barcola made his professional debut for Lyon on 4 November 2021, replacing [[Rayan Cherki]] at the 81st minute of a 3–0 home win against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] in the group stage of the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ferreira|first=Sébastien|date=4 November 2021|title=Résultat et résumé OL - Sparta Prague, Ligue Europa, 4e journée Gr. A|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-europa/2021-2022/ol-sparta-prague-live/527159|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104162636/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-europa/2021-2022/ol-sparta-prague-live/527159 |archive-date=4 November 2021 }}</ref> He managed to provide an assist for [[Karl Toko Ekambi]] on Lyon's third goal, helping his side to a win that would make them the first team to officially qualify for this edition [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivès-Berthet|first=Cyril|date=4 November 2021|title=L'OL qualifié pour les 8es de finale de la Ligue Europa après sa victoire face au Sparta Prague|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-ol-deja-qualifie-pour-les-8es-de-finale-de-la-ligue-europa/1296785|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104200632/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-ol-deja-qualifie-pour-les-8es-de-finale-de-la-ligue-europa/1296785 |archive-date=4 November 2021 }}</ref>

[[File:Barcola vs MHSC 5 avril 2023.png|thumb|upright|Barcola with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] in 2023]]
In January 2023, due to lack of game time with Lyon, Barcola was keen on joining Swiss team [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] on loan. However, the deal collapsed as Lyon were short of attackers after the injury of [[Alexandre Lacazette]] and the departure of [[Karl Toko Ekambi]], which resulted in the integration of Barcola into ''Les Gones'' rotation. Having more playing time during the second half of the [[2022–23 Olympique Lyonnais season|2022–23 season]], Barcola contributed to Lyon's front line alongside top scorer [[Alexandre Lacazette]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blick.ch/fr/sport/football/super_league/saint-gall-avait-senti-le-coup-bradley-barcola-etait-chez-nous-id18907233.html |title=Saint-Gall avait senti le coup: "Bradley Barcola était chez nous..." |website=Blick |language=fr |date=4 September 2023 }}</ref><ref name="june2024">{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/De-la-reserve-lyonnaise-a-un-transfert-de-45-m-et-8364-au-psg-le-mois-qui-a-tout-change-pour-bradley-barcola/1473438 |title=De la réserve lyonnaise, à un transfert de 45 M€ au PSG, le mois qui a tout changé pour Bradley Barcola |website=L'Équipe |language=fr |date=9 June 2024 }}</ref> On 2 April 2023, he scored the only goal to help Lyon defeat the league leader [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] at the [[Parc des Princes]]. A month later, on 7 May 2023, he assisted three goals for Lyon and Lacazette for a comeback win against [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] in a nine-goal thriller, canceling out four goals scored by striker [[Elye Wahi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-ol-arrache-une-victoire-completement-folle-face-a-montpellier-5-4/1395355 |title=L'OL arrache une victoire complètement folle face à Montpellier (5-4) |website=L'Équipe |language=fr |date=7 May 2023 }}</ref> Barcola ended the season with 7 goals and 9 assists across all competitions, being the second most decisive player of the club behind Lacazette.<ref name="june2024"/>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
On 31 August 2023, Barcola joined fellow Ligue 1 club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) for a reported €45 million fee,<ref name=":5">{{cite web |date=31 August 2023 |title=PSG confirm €45m signing of French wonderkid Bradley Barcola from Lyon |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/psg-secure-deal-for-lyon-starlet-bradley-barcola/bltd24f1067c974a9c6 |access-date=31 August 2023 |publisher=Goal.com}}</ref> signing a five-year contract with the club.<ref name=":5" /><ref name=":6" /> He was assigned the number 29 jersey.<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |date=2023-08-31 |title=France U21 international Bradley Barcola joins Paris! |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/bradley-barcola-signs-for-paris-saint-germain-until-2028 |access-date=2023-08-31 |website= |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain |language=en}}</ref> On 3 September, Barcola made his debut as a substitute in a 4–1 away win over his former club Lyon. He became the 500th player to make an appearance for Paris Saint-Germain.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-03 |title=Barcola becomes 500th Paris Saint-Germain player |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/barcola-becomes-500th-paris-saint-germain-player-lyon-psg-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=2023-09-04 |website=EN.PSG.FR |language=en}}</ref> On 24 September, Barcola made his first start for PSG in a 4–0 win over [[Le Classique]] rivals [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcola (PSG) après la victoire contre l'OM : " C'était incroyable " |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Barcola-psg-apres-la-victoire-contre-l-om-c-etait-incroyable/1421822 |access-date=2023-09-24 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 29 October, he recorded his first goal contribution for the club, an assist for [[Warren Zaïre-Emery]]'s opening goal in a 3–2 away win over [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-29 |title=At the end of the suspense, Paris defeats Brest! |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/at-the-end-of-the-suspense-paris-defeats-brest-match-report-paris-saint-germain-brest-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=2023-10-30 |website=EN.PSG.FR |language=en}}</ref> On 9 December, Barcola scored his first goal for PSG in a 2–1 win over [[FC Nantes|Nantes]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 December 2023 |title=PSG-Nantes : magnifique premier but de Bradley Barcola sous le maillot de Paris |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/psg-nantes-magnifique-premier-but-de-bradley-barcola-sous-les-couleurs-parisiennes-09-12-2023-KI6AXX2FHZHYNDVDV7H6OUIUUE.php |access-date=10 December 2023 |website=[[Le Parisien]] |language=Fr}}</ref>

On 14 February 2024, Barcola scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 2–0 victory over [[Real Sociedad]] in the first leg of the round of 16.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=14 February 2024 |title=Bradley Barcola Scores First Champions League Goal With Superb Solo Strike As PSG Beat Real Sociedad |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/video/bradley-barcola-first-champions-league-goal-real-sociedad-psg-highlights |access-date=10 December 2023 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]}}</ref> On 16 April 2024, after his performance in a 4–1 away victory over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the Champions League quarter-finals second leg, Barcola was highly praised in the media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://psgtalk.com/2024/04/psg-bradley-barcola-barcelona-champions-league/|title=PSG Youngster 'Tortured' Barcelona Defense in Second Leg Pundit Says|publisher=PSG Talk|date=22 April 2024 }}</ref> He gave an assist to [[Ousmane Dembélé]] for the equalizing goal in the match, and was key throughout as Paris overturned a 3–2 deficit from the first leg.<ref name="Rutzler">{{Cite web |last=Rutzler |first=Peter |date=1 May 2024 |title=PSG's Bradley Barcola – 'An evolution like his, at a level like this... I've never seen it' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5441293/2024/05/01/psg-bradley-barcola-lyon-ucl/ |work=The New York Times}}</ref> Barcola finished the [[2023–24 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2023–24 season]] with five goals and eight assists in thirty-nine appearances for PSG. On 10 June 2024, he was named by Ligue 1 as the signing of the season.<ref name="PSG Post">{{Cite web |date=10 June 2024 |title=PSG's Bradley Barcola named signing of the season in Ligue 1 |url=https://psgpost.com/posts/psg-s-bradley-barcola-named-signing-of-the-season-in-ligue-1-01j01xbbpsn1 |publisher=PSG Post}}</ref>

On 16 August 2024, Barcola scored his first goal of the season in PSG's Ligue 1 opener away to [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]], an eventual 4–1 victory for the Parisians.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2024-08-17 |title=PSG convincingly thrash Le Havre |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/2488844/psg-convincingly-thrash-le-havre |access-date=2024-08-24 |website=The Express Tribune |language=en}}</ref> On 23 August, he scored the first brace of his career in a 6–0 win over [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] at the [[Parc des Princes]].<ref name="lequipe.fr">{{Cite web |title=Ligue 1 : En pleine confiance, Bradley Barcola a tout pour devenir l'un des leaders de l'attaque du PSG |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/En-pleine-confiance-bradley-barcola-a-tout-pour-devenir-l-un-des-leaders-de-l-attaque-du-psg/1503106 |access-date=2024-08-24 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 22 January 2025, Barcola scored a goal and provided an assist in a 4–2 victory over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Young guns prove PSG can deliver in the Champions League without Mbappé |url=https://apnews.com/article/psg-attack-champions-league-barcola-city-43a66dad09041414cf4ce31086ecad2e |access-date=22 January 2025 |website=[[Associated Press]]|date=22 January 2025 }}</ref> In a 4–1 win over [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] on 8 March 2025, he recorded a goal and an assist, bringing his Ligue 1 tally to 20 goal contributions in a single season for the first time in his career.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Shkura |first=Olga |title=Bradley Barcola reaches 20 goal contributions in single Ligue 1 season for first time |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2025-03-09-bradley-barcola-reaches-20-goal-contributions-in-single-ligue-1-season-for-first-time/ |access-date=2025-04-20 |website=Tribuna.com}}</ref> Barcola helped PSG win a 13th Ligue 1 title and finished the season as the league's second-highest assist provider, with 10 assists, just one behind [[Rayan Cherki]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-17 |title=Ligue 1: Dembélé, Greenwood, Cherki, Barcola... le classement final des meilleurs buteurs et meilleurs passeurs |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/ligue-1-dembele-greenwood-cherki-barcola-le-classement-final-des-meilleurs-buteurs-et-meilleurs-passeurs_AV-202505170396.html |access-date=2025-06-02 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr}}</ref><ref name=":7" /> In the [[2025 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]] on 24 May 2025, he scored two goals and provided an assist in a 3–0 victory over [[Stade de Reims|Reims]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-24 |title=PSG-Reims: le doublé de Barcola, un signal avant la finale de la Ligue des champions |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-des-champions/psg-reims-le-double-de-barcola-un-signal-avant-la-finale-de-la-ligue-des-champions_AV-202505240383.html |access-date=2025-06-02 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr}}</ref> One week later in the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] against [[Inter Milan]], he assisted [[Senny Mayulu]]'s goal, the fifth of a 5–0 victory, winning the competition for the first time in PSG's history and in his career.<ref>{{Cite news |last=O'Neill |first=Caoimhe |date=2025-06-01 |title=The smile of PSG's Senny Mayulu that says everything about Champions League glory |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6394918/2025/06/01/senny-mayulu-psg-champions-league-title/ |access-date=2025-06-02 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Barcola made his 100th official appearance for PSG in a 4–0 win over [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]] in the round of 16 of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]]; this was also his 61st appearance for PSG in the 2024–25 season, surpassing [[Valère Germain]]'s record for most matches in a single season with a Ligue 1 club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4462 |title=Club World Cup statistics (Round of 16, 29 June) |publisher=[[IFFHS]] |date=29 June 2025 |accessdate=2 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Barcola was first selected with [[France national under-18 football team|France under-18]] in January 2020 to play two [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly matches]]. However, he did not appear as most junior encounters were cancelled due to [[COVID-19 pandemic in Europe|COVID-19]] during the following seasons.<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=13 January 2020|title=Sélection : première convocation pour Bradley Barcola|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2020/01/13/selection-premiere-selection-pour-bradley-barcola-avec-la-france-u18|access-date=4 November 2021|website=Olympique Lyonnais|language=fr}}</ref>

On 16 May 2024, Barcola received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|France national team]] for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Euro 2024 : Deschamps convoque Bradley Barcola, Ferland Mendy et N'Golo Kanté dans la liste de l'équipe de France |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Euro-2024-deschamps-convoque-bradley-barcola-ferland-mendy-et-n-golo-kante-dans-la-liste-de-l-equipe-de-france/1468115 |access-date=15 June 2024|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref> On 5 June 2024, he debuted as a substitute for [[Marcus Thuram]] at the 81st minute of a 3–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] victory against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] at [[Stade Saint-Symphorien]] in [[Metz]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Harry|last=Sherlock|title=France player ratings vs Luxembourg: Kylian Mbappe misses chance to fill his boots as blunt Bleus labour to pre-Euro 2024 victory over minnows|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/france-player-ratings-luxembourg-kylian-mbappe-les-bleus-euro-2024/bltbfda123d8685fbfd|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=5 June 2024}}</ref> Barcola recorded his first goal contribution for France by assisting [[Kylian Mbappé]]'s goal, the third of the match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mbappé goal, assists help France win Euro 2024 warm-up|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/701987|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=5 June 2024}}</ref> In the meantime, his club, Paris Saint-Germain, denied him permission to compete in the [[2024 Summer Olympics]] on home soil, along with his teammate Warren Zaïre-Emery.<ref>{{cite web |title=JO : LA PRÉ-LISTE ACTUALISÉE|trans-title=Olympic Games: The preliminary list updated|language=fr|url=https://www.fff.fr/article/12680-jo-la-pre-liste-actualisee.html|publisher=[[French Football Federation]]|date=11 June 2024}}</ref> On 25 June 2024, Barcola made his first start for France on the occasion of his Euro 2024 debut, an eventual 1–1 draw with [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in the third group stage match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-25 |title=Bradley Barcola frustré pour sa première titularisation avec les Bleus |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/france-pologne-bradley-barcola-frustre-pour-sa-premiere-titularisation-avec-les-bleus |access-date=2024-09-06 |website=SOFOOT.com |language=fr}}</ref> He made two additional appearances as a substitute in the competition: 15 minutes against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in the quarter-finals, and 30 minutes against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in the semi-finals, which ended in a 2–1 defeat. Despite his limited playing time, Barcola was praised for making a "strong impression" during the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last= |date=10 July 2024 |title=Euro 2024 - Bleus : Barcola, du gâchis ? |url=https://sports.orange.fr/football/euro/article/euro-2024-bleus-barcola-du-gachis-exclu-CNT000002enp0D.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Orange Actualités |language=fr}}</ref>

On 6 September 2024, at the Parc des Princes, during a [[UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Italy national football team|Italy]], Barcola scored his first international goal just 12 seconds into the game, setting the record for the fastest goal scored by France in the past 90 years,<ref>{{cite news |last=Buxton |first=Richard |date=6 September 2024 |title=Bradley Barcola racks up first senior France goal in memorable fashion⚡️ |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/bradley-barcola-racks-up-first-senior-france-goal-in-memorable-fashion-40001496 |access-date=6 September 2024 |website=OneFootball}}</ref> as well as the fastest goal conceded by Italy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/it-it/sport/calcio/l-gol-lampo-della-francia-all-italia-dopo-14-secondi-erroraccio-di-di-lorenzo-cosa-%C3%A8-successo/ar-AA1q8sn9 |title=l gol lampo della Francia all'Italia, dopo 14' secondi. Erroraccio di Di Lorenzo: cosa è successo |publisher=MSN |language=it |date=6 September 2024 }}</ref> He scored his second international goal against [[Israel national football team|Israel]] later in the next month in the same competition.

==Style of play==
Barcola is a versatile forward who can play on either side of a front three or as a centre forward. Although naturally right-footed, he prefers playing on the left, enabling him to take on opponents one-on-one, cut inside onto his stronger foot, and either shoot, create chances for teammates, or make attacking runs into the box.<ref name="lequipe.fr"/>

Barcola has mentioned drawing inspiration from players like [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]]; in 2020, he stated that he believes his playing style is similar to theirs.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Youcef|first=Rafik|date=31 July 2018|title=Turfu [9/20] - Bradley Barcola (Olympique Lyonnais) : " Je kiffe regarder les vidéos de Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang "|url=https://www.onzemondial.com/france/interview-bradley-barcola-ol-lyon-170750|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=[[Onze Mondial]]|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801113636/http://www.onzemondial.com/france/interview-bradley-barcola-ol-lyon-170750 |archive-date=1 August 2018 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Barcola holds French and Togolese nationalities.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/bradley-barcola-23619/ | title=Bradley BARCOLA - }}</ref> His brother [[Malcolm Barcola|Malcolm]] is also a footballer, and plays for the [[Togo national football team|Togo national team]].<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|date=14 September 2021|title=L'attaquant Bradley Barcola (OL) signe son premier contrat professionnel|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-attaquant-bradley-barcola-ol-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel/1285365|url-status=live|access-date=4 November 2021|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210914120508/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-attaquant-bradley-barcola-ol-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel/1285365 |archive-date=14 September 2021 }}</ref>

